104
00:05:00.265 --> 00:05:03.081
Headings. 
Over here you have this:

105
00:05:03.081 --> 00:05:05.102
"I'm a Heading!" 
little image

106
00:05:05.102 --> 00:05:07.831
that we're going to
talk a little bit about

107
00:05:07.831 --> 00:05:09.064
what headings do for us

108
00:05:09.064 --> 00:05:11.809
and how they give 
content structure.

109
00:05:11.809 --> 00:05:15.128
On the right side
of this slide we have

110
00:05:15.128 --> 00:05:20.509
"The Page Title is an H1" 
and then a little content. 

111
00:05:20.509 --> 00:05:22.730
"Second Level Heading (H2)" 

112
00:05:22.730 --> 00:05:24.792
"Third Level Heading (H3)"

113
00:05:24.792 --> 00:05:28.160
"Another Second Level Heading
for a new section (H2)"

114
00:05:28.160 --> 00:05:31.912
and these are all different, 
well as you can guess, 

115
00:05:31.912 --> 00:05:34.438
headings and we 
have this H1, 2, 3, 

116
00:05:34.438 --> 00:05:36.896
these numbers to 
designate the order

117
00:05:36.896 --> 00:05:40.713
or not the order 
but the importance of

118
00:05:40.713 --> 00:05:42.952
how that content 
is nested

119
00:05:42.952 --> 00:05:44.880
which we'll go over
in a second.

120
00:05:44.880 --> 00:05:48.720
I like to think of headings 
like chapters in a book.

121
00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:52.494
They give the page structure
and the book structure.

122
00:05:52.494 --> 00:05:55.063
The page title would be like
the book title.

123
00:05:55.063 --> 00:05:57.282
It's the biggest,
most important heading.

124
00:05:57.282 --> 00:05:58.960
It defines what
this content is

125
00:05:58.960 --> 00:06:02.479
whereas underneath of that
a second level heading H2

126
00:06:02.479 --> 00:06:07.548
would be like a chapter 
within a book.

127
00:06:07.548 --> 00:06:10.146
It's like they're
important sections

128
00:06:10.146 --> 00:06:12.880
but the book title
is the most important.

129
00:06:12.880 --> 00:06:19.039
An H3 might be a little 
subsection within a chapter.

130
00:06:19.039 --> 00:06:22.266
We have all the way 
down to six, actually, 

131
00:06:22.266 --> 00:06:24.482
that you can use 
but often 

132
00:06:24.482 --> 00:06:28.366
you really only use 
one, two, three sometimes four

133
00:06:28.366 --> 00:06:31.340
but five and six are there
by all means

134
00:06:31.340 --> 00:06:33.581
if you want to
go that far.

135
00:06:33.581 --> 00:06:36.940
The important thing
to remember too here is 

136
00:06:36.940 --> 00:06:39.577
to not choose 
a heading level 

137
00:06:39.577 --> 00:06:43.004
just by the size of 
the text that it is.

138
00:06:43.004 --> 00:06:45.806
We don't want to 
use an H3 in a spot 

139
00:06:45.806 --> 00:06:47.649
where we should 
use an H2

140
00:06:47.649 --> 00:06:51.599
just because we want
a smaller break.

141
00:06:51.599 --> 00:06:57.199
The semantics of the tag, 
the H level, is really important,

142
00:06:57.199 --> 00:07:00.960
and one of the reasons
that this is important is

143
00:07:00.960 --> 00:07:04.319
screen readers can navigate
by heading very easily.

144
00:07:04.319 --> 00:07:06.049
When you go to 
in-page

145
00:07:06.049 --> 00:07:08.240
it's kind of like
skimming the content.

146
00:07:08.240 --> 00:07:09.982
If you're a 
sighted person 

147
00:07:09.982 --> 00:07:12.023
you can go to it, 
scroll down the page, 

148
00:07:12.023 --> 00:07:13.665
look at some of 
the main sections

149
00:07:13.665 --> 00:07:15.968
and say is this a page
I want to be looking at?

150
00:07:15.968 --> 00:07:18.323
Similarly, if you're
using a screen reader

151
00:07:18.323 --> 00:07:20.638
you can press the H key
depending on

152
00:07:20.638 --> 00:07:23.108
the screen reader software
you're using

153
00:07:23.108 --> 00:07:25.819
and it'll jump you 
to those headings

154
00:07:25.819 --> 00:07:27.727
and announce 
the heading level.

155
00:07:27.727 --> 00:07:30.929
You get an idea of the
overall structure of the page

156
00:07:30.929 --> 00:07:33.551
and where you're at
within that as well as 

157
00:07:33.551 --> 00:07:35.990
if this is something
I want to dig in on

158
00:07:35.990 --> 00:07:39.032
or what sections
do I want to explore.

159
00:07:39.032 --> 00:07:44.677
To illustrate what I mean by 
the semantic and the structure

160
00:07:44.677 --> 00:07:47.753
let's take this presentation.
So far, it's called

161
00:07:47.753 --> 00:07:50.319
Creating Accessible Content
with WordPress.

162
00:07:50.319 --> 00:07:54.752
If we weren't to give it
any sort of semantic tag

163
00:07:54.752 --> 00:07:57.676
that H1, it would just be 
at the same level of 

164
00:07:57.676 --> 00:07:59.199
everything underneath of it.

165
00:07:59.199 --> 00:08:03.120
Next we talked about
themes and accessibility,

166
00:08:03.120 --> 00:08:06.720
some content considerations, 

167
00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:09.677
we're going to talk about adding
headings in WordPress next.

168
00:08:09.677 --> 00:08:11.834
You see how you get 
the structure of the page,

169
00:08:11.834 --> 00:08:17.919
kind of a table of contents 
effect is starting to form.

170
00:08:18.240 --> 00:08:21.407
Images and alt text
and then H3 underneath 

171
00:08:21.407 --> 00:08:23.837
of the images
select the alt text.

172
00:08:23.837 --> 00:08:27.054
Just because of the way 
we marked it up 

173
00:08:27.054 --> 00:08:29.329
by creating the 
right heading

174
00:08:29.329 --> 00:08:31.919
we get a lot of
meaning and structure

175
00:08:31.919 --> 00:08:36.320
from the page
just by using those.

176
00:08:36.320 --> 00:08:39.600
In Press (WordPress),
just to quickly go over

177
00:08:39.600 --> 00:08:42.911
in case you're not sure,
there's a heading block

178
00:08:42.911 --> 00:08:45.631
the page title itself
is also a heading

179
00:08:45.631 --> 00:08:49.165
and that's always 
going to be an H1

180
00:08:49.165 --> 00:08:53.055
for pretty much everything.
So you won't need to use H1.

181
00:08:53.055 --> 00:08:55.519
It'll automatically
be your page title.

182
00:08:55.519 --> 00:08:57.814
But you can add
the heading block

183
00:08:57.814 --> 00:09:00.048
and then within
the block toolbar

184
00:09:00.048 --> 00:09:03.781
you have the H2 up here 
in the top part of the toolbar 

185
00:09:03.781 --> 00:09:07.505
as well as in the sidebar 
of the heading settings.

186
00:09:07.505 --> 00:09:09.009
You have your 
H1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6.

187
00:09:09.009 --> 00:09:11.519
You can choose the
one you want.

188
00:09:11.519 --> 00:09:14.459
My preference is using 

189
00:09:14.459 --> 00:09:19.316
the little pound sign 
or number sign. 

190
00:09:19.316 --> 00:09:22.560
It'll automatically,
if you use two of them,

191
00:09:22.560 --> 00:09:25.600
it'll automatically create a
