start looking at? 

546
00:27:44.584 --> 00:27:47.790
Looking at accessibility 
and evaluating it 

547
00:27:47.790 --> 00:27:51.523
for accessibility first, 
is such an easy way

548
00:27:51.523 --> 00:27:53.746
to eliminate, 
I'd say, 

549
00:27:53.746 --> 00:27:57.287
90 plus percent of 
plugins or themes. 

550
00:27:57.287 --> 00:28:02.125
If you go to it and test it 
with a few things 

551
00:28:02.125 --> 00:28:07.520
you will narrow down your pool 
dramatically, very quickly.

552
00:28:07.520 --> 00:28:10.987
I call this the 
5 Minute Accessibility Audit.

553
00:28:10.987 --> 00:28:15.688
I test the keyboard interactions
using Tab and Arrow keys.

554
00:28:15.688 --> 00:28:20.674
I zoom in and out on it
to see if it breaks the functionality,

555
00:28:20.674 --> 00:28:22.882
see if they've 
labeled inputs. 

556
00:28:22.882 --> 00:28:25.159
Inputs here are like 
form fields. 

557
00:28:25.159 --> 00:28:27.887
We'll talk about 
all these in a minute 

558
00:28:27.887 --> 00:28:29.661
and see how they use color.

559
00:28:29.661 --> 00:28:31.672
Do they use
color appropriately,

560
00:28:31.672 --> 00:28:35.931
contrast as well as 
if they used color

561
00:28:35.931 --> 00:28:40.473
to signify a meaning
without the supporting text.

562
00:28:40.473 --> 00:28:44.553
First we have our
keyboard navigation.

563
00:28:44.553 --> 00:28:49.942
I have this Twitter navigation here
and if you press Tab on it,

564
00:28:49.942 --> 00:28:52.807
