that focus ring

565
00:28:52.807 --> 00:28:54.492
and that focus ring 

566
00:28:54.492 --> 00:28:58.115
tells you where you are
on the page as well.

567
00:28:58.115 --> 00:29:01.712
It should be 
very visible, easy to see

568
00:29:01.712 --> 00:29:04.559
and it should allow you
to move around

569
00:29:04.559 --> 00:29:06.464
just using your keyboard. 

570
00:29:06.464 --> 00:29:09.033
As a sighted keyboard person 

571
00:29:09.033 --> 00:29:12.489
you would just use Tab 
most of the time.

572
00:29:12.489 --> 00:29:17.729
If you're in a radio group 
or a dropdown, you might 

573
00:29:17.729 --> 00:29:20.829
use up and down arrows 
or right and left. 

574
00:29:20.829 --> 00:29:24.974
If you reach something
and you're not sure

575
00:29:24.974 --> 00:29:26.659
how to interact with it, 

576
00:29:26.659 --> 00:29:28.706
try using the arrow keys 

577
00:29:28.706 --> 00:29:31.549
and see if you 
get somewhere else. 

578
00:29:31.549 --> 00:29:35.806
Zooming in and out of things. 
When you zoom in and out 

579
00:29:35.806 --> 00:29:37.343
it should increase 
the size of the text 

580
00:29:37.343 --> 00:29:41.782
and reflow content, 
if necessary.

581
00:29:41.782 --> 00:29:43.992
This is an example 
of a website. 

582
00:29:43.992 --> 00:29:46.266
Just pressing Command plus on a Mac

583
00:29:46.266 --> 00:29:48.834
and it zooms in
and you can see

584
00:29:48.834 --> 00:29:55.840
the header reflows to 
accommodate the larger text.

585
00:29:57.520 --> 00:29:59.264
Labeling inputs. 

586
00:29:59.264 --> 00:30:02.240
We see here,
we have this form

587
00:30:02.240 --> 00:30:06.728
that has the Email, 
Confirm email, Password

588
00:30:06.728 --> 00:30:10.507
and you see they're
inside of the box.

589
00:30:10.507 --> 00:30:14.559
Labels: 
we need to describe the field

590
00:30:14.559 --> 00:30:17.964
but these, 
inside of the input field,

591
00:30:17.964 --> 00:30:20.578
are actually placeholders. 

592
00:30:20.578 --> 00:30:22.320
They're not labels.

593
00:30:22.320 --> 00:30:26.639
Placeholders, 
they're not actually necessary 

594
00:30:26.639 --> 00:30:30.823
but if you use them, 
they are examples of the text.

595
00:30:30.823 --> 00:30:38.434
Instead of Email there, 
it should say example@gmail.com.

596
00:30:38.434 --> 00:30:40.402
A placeholder is 
supposed to be an example 

597
00:30:40.402 --> 00:30:42.194
of the content 
to be filled in there.

598
00:30:42.194 --> 00:30:44.726
The bigger issue 
here is that 

599
00:30:44.726 --> 00:30:46.851
once you click into 
that field 

600
00:30:46.851 --> 00:30:49.251
or you start typing 
in that field, 

601
00:30:49.251 --> 00:30:50.831
your label is now gone.

602
00:30:50.831 --> 00:30:53.853
A much better way
to do it is to have 

603
00:30:53.853 --> 00:30:57.910
the label coded correctly
and outside of that input.

604
00:30:57.910 --> 00:31:00.880
That way when 
you're typing into it

605
00:31:00.880 --> 00:31:05.008
you can still
see the label appropriately.

606
00:31:05.008 --> 00:31:09.248
To demonstrate why,
see if you can remember

607
00:31:09.248 --> 00:31:11.279
what this field was for.

608
00:31:11.279 --> 00:31:15.804
Now there's text in it.
The label is gone.

609
00:31:15.804 --> 00:31:19.360
If you happen 
to remember,

610
00:31:19.360 --> 00:31:24.960
it was the name field,
"What should we call you?"

611
00:31:25.120 --> 00:31:29.600
It's really important to 
have those labels visible.

612
00:31:29.600 --> 00:31:31.567
Now would be a time, 

613
